Bring a large #saucepan{} of water to the boil with @salt{1/2%tsp}. When boiling,
add the @penne pasta{180%g} to the water and bring back to the boil. Cook until
tender, ~{12%minutes}. Once cooked, drain in a #colander{} and pop back into the
pan. Drizzle with @oil{} and stir through to stop it sticking together.

Meanwhile, peel and grate the @garlic clove{1}(peeled and grated) (or use a
#garlic press{}).

Heat a drizzle of @oil{} in a large #frying pan{} on medium-high heat. Once hot,
add the @diced British chicken breast{1%pack} and season with @salt{1/4%tsp} and
@black pepper{1/4%tsp}. IMPORTANT: Wash your hands and equipment after handling
raw chicken and its packaging. Fry until golden brown on the outside,
~{5-6%minutes}.

Add the garlic and @Cajun spice mix{1%sachet} (add less if you'd prefer things
milder) to the chicken. Cook, stirring frequently, for ~{1%minute}. Stir in the
@tomato passata{1%carton}, @water for the sauce{100%ml} and the
@chicken stock paste{10%g}. Bring to the boil, then lower the heat. Simmer,
stirring occasionally, until thickened, ~{5-6%minutes}.

Once the sauce has thickened, stir through half the
@grated hard Italian style cheese{20%g}, followed by the @creme fraiche{75%g}.
Bring to the boil, stirring, then remove from the heat. IMPORTANT: The chicken
is cooked when no longer pink in the middle. Taste and season with @salt{} and
@pepper{} if needed.

Add the cooked pasta to the creamy sauce and mix well to combine. Reheat until
piping hot if needed. Share the creamy Cajun chicken pasta between your #bowls{}.
Sprinkle over the remaining cheese to finish. Enjoy!

> This Creamy Cajun Chicken Breast Pasta is a crowd pleaser and is one to get the
> family round the dinner table for. Super simple to make, and easily customised
> to suit the kids too.